# Accessibility Rules

## HTML
- Use semantic HTML: button, nav, main, header, footer, section, article
- Never use div or span as interactive elements
- Every image needs alt attribute (empty alt="" for decorative images)
- Heading hierarchy must be logical: h1 → h2 → h3, no skipping levels

## Forms
- Every input must have associated label with matching for/id
- Never use placeholder as the only label
- Required fields must have aria-required="true"
- Error messages must be linked to inputs via aria-describedby

## Interactive elements
- Touch targets minimum 44x44px
- Focus styles must be visible — never remove outline without replacement
- Buttons must have descriptive text or aria-label

## Color & contrast
- Text contrast minimum 4.5:1 (normal text), 3:1 (large text 18px+)
- Never convey information by color alone

## Angular specific
- Use [attr.aria-*] for dynamic ARIA attributes
- RouterLink elements must have descriptive text